Date: 0/0/1951
Source: Radio NZ / National Radio
Author:
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote: After the logs were cut, each was sniped. To snipe a log, the end is chipped all the way round so that it can be handled without catching humps in the ground, stumps and so on; in fact you might say that a log when it is sniped looks rather like the blunt end of a whale.
Notes: H.S. McCarroll The Days of the Kauri Bushmen [Radio Talk 2: TS]

